p loader, it looks like that Class.forName should find it with the delegating loader as the parent. So, all that makes sense! I think I'm on the right track here.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_OVXkr3nGrv5w6xDtCGiZHUw8|fc_042f96228ff25e2b0169f9c09fcfd8819eb3a2bf06603d618d", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.springframework/spring-core/5.3.15/src/test/java/org_springframework/spring_core/ReflectUtilsTest.java", "offset": 1, "limit": 35}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1108, "output": 4000, "cacheRead": 35840, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 40948, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777975397496, "responseId": "resp_042f96228ff25e2b0169f9c0660ee4819ea7a536d0ee969409"}}
